{"key":"post-8345288","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8345288</id>\n<content>It doesn't really hurt if water touches the bottom of a quart/liter jar, but for growers using the pf tek with 1/2 pint jars, any water touching the bottom of the jar can easily boil up and over the top, ruining the mixture inside the jar.  That's why we recommend elevating the jars totally out of the water.  &lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8345292</next>\n<prev>8345263</prev>\n<first>8345152</first>\n<last>8345330</last>\n<when>1209563904</when>\n<utime>04/30/08 04:58 PM</utime>\n</post>"}